Users are not able to login to User Console associated with an Eucalyptus 3.3 LDAP/AD integrated cloud.

Observations below:

{code}
And also worth mentioning, when I use “password” or any invalid password, I get an exception in the logs indicating and invalid login/password from LDAP. When I use the correct LDAP password, I don’t get any errors/exceptions in the logs, only an error in the dashboard login GUI (User Console). This leads me to believe the AD authentication is working, but Euca doesn’t know how to process it. Here’s the policy assigned to the euca-admin group.

{"Version":"2008-10-17","Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow", "Action":["*"], "Resource":["*"]}]}

And just realized when pulling this policy from the Admin GUI, that the user LDAP authentication works for Admin GUI but not the Dashboard (User Console). How do I fix that? It appears the login profile I created only allows access to Admin GUI, but really need Dashboard (User Console) access for these users.
{code}

